# IntradayNet — Dedicated Intraday Model Architecture Plan

> **Status**: Research & Design (not yet implemented)
> **Data**: 499 stocks × 1-minute bars × 2015–2026 (~100K bars/stock/year)
> **Goal**: Best possible intraday prediction system for Indian equities

---

## 1. Why a Separate Intraday Model?

The current StockXpert model was designed for **daily-scale** predictions. For intraday trading, it has fundamental mismatches:

| Dimension | Daily Model (StockXpert) | Intraday Model (Proposed) |
|-----------|--------------------------|---------------------------|
| **Input granularity** | Daily OHLCV (1 bar/day) | 1-minute OHLCV (375 bars/day) |
| **Prediction horizons** | 1-10 days | 15min / 30min / 60min / EOD |
| **Feature timescale** | RSI-14 (14 days), SMA-50 (50 days) | RSI-14 (14 minutes), EMA-9 (9 minutes) |
| **Key patterns** | Multi-day trends, breakouts | ORB, VWAP cross, momentum bursts |
| **Session awareness** | None | Time-of-day matters enormously |
| **Training samples** | ~2,500 per stock (10 yrs daily) | ~900,000 per stock (10 yrs × ~375 bars/day) |
| **Sentiment horizon** | Overnight + multi-day | Pre-market + intraday headlines |

The massive difference in **data volume** (375x more bars) and **temporal dynamics** (sub-hour patterns) means we need a purpose-built architecture.

---

