## 4. Recommended Approach: Multi-Architecture Tournament

Rather than picking one architecture upfront, we run a **tournament** to find empirically which works best on our data.

### 4.1 Tournament Design

```
Phase 1: Quick Screening (subset data)
  ├─ Train all 6 architectures on 20 liquid stocks × 2 years (2022-2023)
  ├─ Validate on 2024 H1
  ├─ Compare: H1 direction accuracy, Sharpe ratio, training time
  └─ Eliminate bottom 3 architectures

Phase 2: Full Training (top 3)
  ├─ Train top 3 on 100 stocks × 5 years (2019-2023)
  ├─ Validate on 2024
  ├─ Test on 2025 (sealed)
  └─ Select winner + runner-up

Phase 3: Full-Scale Training (winner)
  ├─ Train winner on 499 stocks × 8 years (2015-2023)
  ├─ Walk-forward validation (yearly re-train)
  └─ Final backtest on 2025

Phase 4: Ensemble (optional)
  ├─ Combine winner + runner-up predictions
  ├─ Weighted average or stacking
  └─ Test if ensemble beats single model
```

### 4.2 Fixed Evaluation Protocol

All models tested under identical conditions:

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Input sequence** | Last 120 minute bars (~2 hours) |
| **Prediction horizons** | 15min, 30min, 60min, EOD |
| **Training data** | Standardized per tournament phase |
| **Batch size** | 512 |
| **Max epochs** | 50 (early stopping, patience=10) |
| **Optimizer** | AdamW (lr=3e-4, wd=1e-4) |
| **Loss** | Direction (focal) + Magnitude (L1) + Confidence (BCE) |
| **Evaluation metric** | Direction accuracy (primary), IC, Sharpe (secondary) |
| **Normalization** | RobustScaler per feature, fit on train only |

---

## 5. Sentiment & News Integration

### 5.1 The Challenge for Intraday

For daily predictions, overnight sentiment accumulates and affects next-day opens. For **intraday**, the dynamics are different:

| Timing | Sentiment Source | Impact |
|--------|-----------------|--------|
| **Pre-market** (7-9:15 AM) | Overnight news, global markets | Gap open, first-hour direction |
| **During session** (9:15-3:30) | Breaking headlines, sector news | Intraday momentum shifts |
| **After close** (3:30-7 PM) | Results announcements, policy news | Next-day gap (less relevant for intraday) |

### 5.2 Sentiment Integration Architecture

We propose a **3-stream sentiment module**:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│            SENTIMENT FUSION MODULE               │
│                                                  │
│  Stream 1: Pre-Market Sentiment                  │
│  ├─ Overnight news headlines (GDELT, Google RSS) │
│  ├─ FinBERT scores aggregated to stock-level     │
│  ├─ Global market indicators (US close, Asia)    │
│  └─ Output: (B, 8) pre-market sentiment vector   │
│                                                  │
│  Stream 2: Historical Sentiment Context          │
│  ├─ 5-day rolling sentiment (from CSV data)      │
│  ├─ Sentiment momentum (5d vs 21d)               │
│  ├─ Sentiment spike indicator                    │
│  ├─ Sentiment-price divergence                   │
│  └─ Output: (B, 6) historical context vector     │
│                                                  │
│  Stream 3: Market Regime Context                 │
│  ├─ NIFTY 50 intraday trend (up/down/flat)       │
│  ├─ Sector index performance today               │
│  ├─ VIX level and change                         │
│  ├─ Advance-decline ratio                        │
│  └─ Output: (B, 6) market context vector         │
│                                                  │
│  Fusion: Concat(S1, S2, S3) → MLP → (B, 32)     │
│  Injected into main model as context features    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 5.3 Sentiment Features for Intraday

| # | Feature | Source | Description |
|---|---------|--------|-------------|
| 1 | `premarket_sentiment` | FinBERT / Google News | Avg sentiment of last 12h headlines |
| 2 | `premarket_sentiment_count` | News count | Number of headlines (more = more volatile) |
| 3 | `premarket_sentiment_max` | Max score | Strongest single headline sentiment |
| 4 | `premarket_sentiment_std` | Score std | Controversy indicator |
| 5 | `sentiment_5d_avg` | CSV data | 5-day rolling average sentiment |
| 6 | `sentiment_momentum` | CSV data | 5d avg - 21d avg |
| 7 | `sentiment_spike` | CSV data | Today vs 5d avg (> 2σ = spike) |
| 8 | `sentiment_price_div` | Derived | Sentiment direction ≠ price direction |
| 9 | `nifty_intraday_return` | Index data | NIFTY 50 return since open |
| 10 | `sector_intraday_return` | Index data | Stock's sector index return since open |
| 11 | `vix_level` | Index data | India VIX (fear gauge) |
| 12 | `vix_change` | Index data | VIX change from yesterday |
| 13 | `market_breadth` | Derived | Advance-decline ratio |
| 14 | `global_cue` | Derived | US futures / Asia market overnight return |

### 5.4 How Sentiment Enters Each Architecture

| Architecture | Integration Method |
|-------------|-------------------|
| **TCN + Attention** | Concat with TCN output before final MLP |
| **TFT** | Static covariates (stock-level) + known future inputs (time-based) |
| **CNN-BiLSTM** | Inject as initial hidden state of BiLSTM |
| **Transformer** | Extra CLS-like tokens appended to sequence |
| **WaveNet** | Conditioning vector multiplied with skip connections |
| **Mamba** | Concatenated to input features at each timestep |

