## 7. Training Methodology

### 7.1 Data Pipeline

```
For each stock:
  1. Load minute CSV → Filter to market hours (9:15-15:30)
  2. Compute 25 per-bar features
  3. Compute session context (20 features)
  4. Generate samples:
     - Input: (120 bars × 25 features) + (20 context features) + (14 sentiment features)
     - Target: direction + magnitude at 15m, 30m, 60m, EOD
  5. Sample every 15 minutes within each session (avoid overlapping targets)
```

### 7.2 Target Construction

| Horizon | Target Return | Direction Label | Sample Rate |
|---------|--------------|-----------------|-------------|
| **15 min** | (Close_{t+15} - Close_t) / Close_t | 1 if > 0, else 0 | Every 15 bars |
| **30 min** | (Close_{t+30} - Close_t) / Close_t | 1 if > 0, else 0 | Every 15 bars |
| **60 min** | (Close_{t+60} - Close_t) / Close_t | 1 if > 0, else 0 | Every 15 bars |
| **EOD** | (Close_EOD - Close_t) / Close_t | 1 if > 0, else 0 | Every 15 bars |

> [!NOTE]
> We skip samples from the last 60 minutes of the session (after 2:30 PM) for the 60-min and EOD targets to avoid lookahead bias from market close mechanics.

### 7.3 Train/Val/Test Splits

| Split | Period | Purpose |
|-------|--------|---------|
| **Train** | 2015-01-01 to 2023-12-31 | Model fitting |
| **Validation** | 2024-01-01 to 2024-12-31 | Hyperparameter tuning, early stopping |
| **Test** | 2025-01-01 to 2025-12-31 | Final sealed evaluation |

### 7.4 Training Considerations

**Handling 499 stocks × 9 years of minute data**:

1. **Lazy loading**: Don't load all data into memory. Use memory-mapped files or chunked reading.
2. **Per-stock batching**: Each mini-batch contains samples from multiple stocks for diversity.
3. **Session-aware sampling**: Sample from different sessions and stocks uniformly.
4. **Data augmentation**:
   - Time warping (stretch/compress minute sequences by ±10%)
   - Volume scaling (random ×0.8-1.2 to simulate different liquidity)
   - Random session cropping (start from random bar within first hour)
5. **Curriculum learning**: Start with high-volume liquid stocks (Nifty 50), gradually add midcaps.

### 7.5 Loss Function

Same multi-task structure as StockXpert, adapted for intraday:

```
L = w_dir × FocalLoss(direction_logits, direction_targets)    # 0.5
  + w_mag × HuberLoss(magnitude_pred, magnitude_targets)      # 0.3
  + w_conf × BCE(confidence, was_correct_direction)            # 0.2
  + w_vwap × L1Loss(vwap_target_pred, eod_vwap_deviation)     # 0.1
```

**Intraday-specific additions**:
- **Time-weighted loss**: Predictions near market open (9:15-10:00) get 1.5× weight (most actionable)
- **Liquidity-weighted loss**: High-volume stocks get slightly more weight (more tradeable)

---

## 8. Intraday Backtesting Strategy

### 8.1 Simulation Rules

| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| **Trading hours** | 9:30 AM – 3:15 PM (skip first 15 min, last 15 min) |
| **Entry** | When model confidence ≥ threshold |
| **Exit** | At prediction horizon OR stop-loss OR EOD (mandatory) |
| **Position sizing** | Fixed ₹1L per trade (or configurable) |
| **Max concurrent** | 3 positions |
| **Brokerage** | ₹20 per order (flat, like Zerodha) |
| **STT** | 0.025% on sell side |
| **Slippage** | 0.05% per trade |
| **Stop loss** | 0.5% (tight, intraday) |

### 8.2 Strategy Variants

| Strategy | Entry Logic | Exit Logic | Expected Trades/Day |
|----------|------------|------------|---------------------|
| **Scalp** | 15-min P(up) ≥ 0.7 | 15-min horizon or 0.3% SL | 5-10 |
| **Momentum** | 30-min P(up) ≥ 0.65 + volume > 1.5× avg | 30-min horizon or 0.5% SL | 3-5 |
| **Swing Intra** | 60-min P(up) ≥ 0.60 + trend alignment | 60-min horizon or 0.7% SL | 2-3 |
| **EOD Position** | EOD P(up) ≥ 0.60 + morning entry | 3:15 PM mandatory close | 1-2 |

