| IntradayNet model | `models/intraday_model.py` | TCN/TFT/etc architecture |
| Intraday features V2 | `features/intraday_features_v2.py` | Per-bar feature computation |
| Intraday dataset | `dataset/intraday_dataset.py` | PyTorch Dataset for minute data |
| Intraday training | `scripts/train_intraday.py` | Training script |
| Intraday backtester | `scripts/backtest_intraday.py` | Minute-level simulation |
| Intraday config | `configs/intraday_backtest.yaml` | Model + training config |

---

## 10. Recommendation: Phased Approach

### Phase 1: Quick Win — TCN + Attention
Start with **Architecture A (TCN + Attention)** because:
- Fastest to train on CPU
- Lowest overfitting risk for our noisy data
- Simple to implement and debug
- Good baseline to beat

### Phase 2: Challenge — TFT or CNN-BiLSTM
Train the **runner-up** to see if extra complexity helps:
- TFT if we want interpretability (know WHY the model predicts)
- CNN-BiLSTM if we want a battle-tested approach

### Phase 3: Ensemble
Combine top 2 models for potentially better performance.

### Phase 4: Full Scale
Train winner on all 499 stocks with walk-forward validation.

---

> [!TIP]
> **Before building any model**: Run the 499-stock backtest with the existing daily model first. If the daily model's H1 prediction already gives >60% hit rate on intraday entry timing, the marginal benefit of a dedicated intraday model may be smaller than expected. Let the data decide.
